Date: Mon, 14 Apr 2008 15:31:39
From: Tatiana Lando [tatiana.lando@gmail.com]
Subject: Young Scientists Conference in Information Retrieval
E-mail this message to a friend:
http://linguistlist.org/issues/emailmessage/verification.cfm?iss=19-1270.html&submissionid=175221&topicid=3&msgnumber=1  

Full Title: Young Scientists Conference in Information Retrieval 

Date: 01-Sep-2008 - 05-Sep-2008
Location: Taganrog, Russia 
Contact Person: Tatiana Lando
Meeting Email: russir-session@googlegroups.com
Web Site: http://www.romip.ru/russir2008 

Linguistic Field(s): Applied Linguistics; Computational Linguistics 

Call Deadline: 01-Jun-2008 

Meeting Description:

Conference for Young Scientists in Information Retrieval 
In the framework of the 2nd Russian Summer School in Information Retrieval
(http://www.romip.ru/russir2008)
1-5 September 2008 
Taganrog

Organizers:
Non-commercial partnership ROMIP 
Taganrog Technological Institute of Southern Federal University. 

Call for Papers

The conference is aimed at: 
- Support and intensification of the research in the field of Information
Retrieval in Russia
- Creation of the young scientists community in the field of Information
Retrieval, broadening the network of the interuniversity relations between
researchers working in this field
- Helping young scientists in mastering public scientific speaking at the
conferences and workshops, discussing works with participation of the
specialists in Information Retrieval
  
Graduate and postgraduate students, young researchers from academia and industry
(under 27 years old), working in the field of Information Retrieval are welcome
to participate in the conference.

General topics of the conference: 
- Theory and models of Information Retrieval
- Algorithms and data structures for Information Retrieval
- Text Information Retrieval
- Multimedia search
- Text processing in Information Retrieval tasks
- User interfaces for Information Retrieval
- Web search
- Fact extraction, text mining
- Methods of the Information Retrieval evaluation 

Papers should be submitted in Russian or English and should not exceed 15 pages.
Please, follow the guidelines provided in the example on the web-page:
http://agora.guru.ru/russir-kmu-2008 

All the submitted scientific papers will be reviewed by the Program Committee
with the assistance of external reviewers. 

The authors of the selected papers will be invited to the conference to present
their work in oral or poster sessions. We also plan to publish the proceedings
of the conference. 

Important Dates: 
1st June 2008 Paper Submission Deadline
1st July 2008 Notification of Acceptance
1st August 2008 Camera-ready Papers

Paper submitting for the conference is not a requirement for the participation
in the 2nd Russian Summer School in Information Retrieval. Organizers plan to
establish a limited number of grants to cover transport and accommodation
expenses of the school participants. The authors of the papers selected for the
conference will have preferences when considering grant applications. 

To submit a paper please contact the organizing committee:
russir-session@googlegroups.com.



	
